%python
import numpy as nu
import pandas as pa
import seaborn as sns
sns.set()
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import plotly as plotly
import plotly.express as px
import plotly.graph_objects as go
import plotly.offline as pyo
from plotly.offline import init_notebook_mode, iplot, plot

data = pa.read_csv('/root/dataset/listings.csv')

paragraphs.title: 1. Total number of rentals that are available 365 days a year, and the total number of rentals
paragraphs.text:
%python

# total number of rentals that are available 365 days a year

renting_out_365 = nu.array(data['availability_365']==365).sum()
print(renting_out_365)

%python

# total number of rentals

total_renting_out = nu.array(data['availability_365']).sum().round(2)
print(total_renting_out)

paragraphs.title: 2. Number of rentals per neighbourhood_group
paragraphs.text:
%python

plt.figure(figsize=(10,4))
sns.countplot(data.sort_values('neighbourhood_group').neighbourhood_group,hue=data.room_type,palette='Set1')
plt.title('Number of rentals per neighbourhood_group')
plt.xlabel('Neighbourhood Group')
plt.ylabel('Number of rentals')
plt.show()

paragraphs.title: 3. Average price of Private room rental by neighbourhood_group
paragraphs.text:
%python

data_fr1 = data[data.room_type == "Private room"][["neighbourhood_group","price"]]
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5))
sns.barplot(x="neighbourhood_group", y="price", data=data_fr1)
plt.show()

paragraphs.title: 5. lowest price rentals per each room_type
6. Percentage of owners who rent more than one property
paragraphs.text:
%python

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7,7))

list_per_owner = (data.groupby('host_id').size())

pie_data = (list_per_owner.pipe(pa.cut, bins=[1,2,3,5,1000], include_lowest=True, right=False,labels=['1_property', '2_properties', 'upto_3-4', 'above_5+']).value_counts())

pie_data.plot(kind='pie',
              explode=(0.01, ) * len(pie_data),
              autopct=lambda v: (
                  '{}'.format(int(v/100*sum(pie_data))) +
                  '\n' + '({:.1%})'.format(v/100)),)

ax.set_ylabel('')
ax.set_title('Percentage of owners who rent more than one property', weight='bold')

plt.show()

hosts = data.groupby('host_id').size().reset_index(name='calculated_host_listings_count')
hosts = hosts.sort_values(by=['calculated_host_listings_count'],ascending=False)

print('{}% hosts have more than one listing.'.format(int(round(hosts[hosts['calculated_host_listings_count']>=2].host_id.count()*100/hosts.host_id.count()))))
